            <title>[CAMEL-5024] Streaming splitter ignores exception handling</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-5024</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If an exception occurs on the next() call of an Iterator in a streaming splitter, the exception is never propagated to the exception or the error handler. This will lead to improper route termination, and inifite rollback/retry cycles.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I attached the minimal test case demonstrating the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Ubuntu Linux&lt;br/&gt;
Java version &quot;1.6.0_24&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
